# Mobile App — Expo & React Native Conventions

Applies to everything under `apps/mobile/`. The mobile app is the
**staff-facing** surface: shift viewing, exchange requests, time-off
submissions. Managers and owners may use it too, but **write-heavy
management lives in the web dashboard** and stays gated server-side.

---

## Framework baseline

| Aspect | Value | Notes |
|--------|-------|-------|
| Expo SDK | **54** (`expo@~54.0`) | New Architecture (`newArchEnabled: true`) |
| React Native | **0.81** | React 19.1 |
| Router | **Expo Router** (file-based) | Stack + Tabs under `app/` |
| Auth | `@clerk/clerk-expo` | `ClerkProvider` with `tokenCache` |
| Secure storage | `expo-secure-store` | Backs `tokenCache` |
| Styling | **NativeWind 5 (preview)** + Tailwind CSS v4 | `global.css` + `@sous/config/tailwind-preset` |
| Client state | **Zustand** | Feature-local stores in `features/<x>/store.ts` |
| Server state | TanStack Query v5 | Feature-local `queryFn`s in `features/<x>/api.ts` |
| HTTP | Axios singleton | `lib/api-client.ts` with Clerk JWT interceptor |
| Types | `@sous/types` (shared with web) | No server code — API clients only |

### Environment variables

The mobile app reads **`apps/mobile/.env`** (Expo convention). It is
generated by `./setup-agent-envs.sh` from `MOBILE_*` host variables.

- Anything the JS bundle must see **must** be prefixed `EXPO_PUBLIC_*`.
  Non-prefixed values are dropped from the client bundle.
- Required: `EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL`.
- The app `throw`s from `app/_layout.tsx` if the Clerk key is missing —
  don't rely on silent fallbacks.

### React version — do NOT bump in isolation

React Native 0.81.5 (Expo SDK 54) ships a renderer pinned to
**React 19.1.0**. Any other React version crashes the bundle with
`Incompatible React versions` at startup.

- `react` and `react-dom` are pinned to `19.1.0` in **both** apps and
  force-deduped tree-wide by the root `package.json` `overrides` block
  (plus a declared root `dependencies` entry so npm can't hoist a
  different peer-only copy).
- `apps/mobile/metro.config.js` additionally aliases `react`,
  `react-dom`, `react-native`, `scheduler`, and `@clerk/clerk-expo`
  to their single resolved directory so Metro never bundles two
  instances — even if a future hoist ever goes wrong.
- `scripts/verify-react-singletons.mjs` runs on `postinstall` and
  fails the install if any of those singletons diverge. If it fires,
  check what new dependency pulled in a broader `react` peer and
  either pin that dep to an Expo-SDK-54-compatible version, or
  coordinate a full Expo/React upgrade of **both** apps together.
- When adding a mobile dep that touches React internals, use
  `npx expo install <pkg>` from `apps/mobile` so Expo picks an
  SDK-54-aligned version (same principle for `@react-native-*`).

