## Directory layout

```
apps/mobile/
├── app/                       Expo Router file-based routes
│   ├── _layout.tsx            ClerkProvider + QueryClient + AuthGate + Stack
│   ├── (auth)/                Unauthenticated surfaces (sign-in, forgot password)
│   │   ├── _layout.tsx
│   │   ├── sign-in.tsx
│   │   └── forgot-password.tsx
│   └── (tabs)/                Authenticated tabs (home, schedule, exchange, time-off)
│       ├── _layout.tsx        Tab bar config
│       ├── index.tsx          Home
│       ├── schedule.tsx
│       ├── exchange.tsx
│       └── time-off.tsx
├── features/                  Feature modules (primary code location)
│   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── api.ts             fetchMembership
│   │   ├── store.ts           Zustand (membership + pending sign-in error)
│   │   └── screens/           sign-in-screen, forgot-password-screen
│   ├── home/                  api.ts, screens/, components/
│   ├── schedule/              api.ts, screens/, components/
│   ├── exchange/              api.ts, screens/, components/
│   └── time-off/              api.ts, screens/, components/
├── components/                Shared UI (text, screen-wrapper, icon-symbol, haptic-tab, ui/)
├── hooks/                     use-color-scheme, use-theme-color
├── lib/                       api-client, query-client, token-cache
├── constants/                 Colors/theme constants
├── global.css                 NativeWind v4 theme tokens (mirrors web)
├── tailwind.config.js         Uses @sous/config preset
├── metro.config.js            Metro + NativeWind config
├── app.json                   Expo config (newArchEnabled, plugins)
└── .env                       Generated — do not hand-edit
```

**Rule:** the routing tree in `app/` is **thin**. Each route file
typically renders a single `<XScreen />` component from
`features/<x>/screens/`. Business logic, data fetching, and UI live in
`features/`, not in `app/`.

